  "modules": [
    {
      "module_id": "m1",
      "title": "Time Value of Money",
      "topics": [
        {
          "topic_id": "t1",
          "title": "Concept of Time Value of Money",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "estimated_time": "20 min",
          "prerequisites": [],
          "learning_outcomes": [
            "Understand why money has time value",
            "Compare present and future value"
          ],
          "content": "## Time Value of Money (TVM)\nThe concept states that money available today is worth more than the same amount in the future due to its earning potential.\n\n### Reasons\n- Inflation\n- Opportunity cost\n- Risk\n\n### Key Concepts\n- Present Value (PV)\n- Future Value (FV)\n\n### Example\n₹100 today is worth more than ₹100 after one year because it can be invested.",
          "examples": [
            "Investing money in a bank",
            "Delaying payment reduces value"
          ],
          "common_mistakes": [
            "Ignoring inflation",
            "Comparing future money directly with present"
          ],
          "qna": [
            {
              "q": "What is TVM?",
              "a": "Money today is worth more than future money."
            },
            {
              "q": "Why does money have time value?",
              "a": "Due to inflation and opportunity cost."
            },
            {
              "q": "What is present value?",
              "a": "Current worth of future money."
            },
            { "q": "What is future value?", "a": "Value of money in future." },
            { "q": "Example?", "a": "₹100 today vs ₹100 next year." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic_id": "t2",
          "title": "Compounding and Discounting",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "estimated_time": "25 min",
          "prerequisites": ["t1"],
          "learning_outcomes": [
            "Apply compounding and discounting",
            "Calculate future and present values"
          ],
          "content": "## Compounding and Discounting\nCompounding calculates future value, while discounting calculates present value.\n\n### Compounding\nFV = PV × (1 + r)^n\n\n### Discounting\nPV = FV / (1 + r)^n\n\n### Importance\nUsed in investment decisions.",
          "examples": ["Fixed deposits", "Loan calculations"],
          "common_mistakes": [
            "Using wrong rate",
            "Ignoring compounding periods"
          ],
          "qna": [
            { "q": "What is compounding?", "a": "Calculating future value." },
            { "q": "What is discounting?", "a": "Calculating present value." },
            { "q": "Formula for FV?", "a": "PV(1+r)^n." },
            { "q": "Why important?", "a": "Investment decisions." },
            { "q": "Example?", "a": "Bank interest." }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "module_id": "m2",
      "title": "Capital Budgeting",
      "topics": [
        {
          "topic_id": "t1",
          "title": "Capital Budgeting Techniques",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "estimated_time": "25 min",
          "prerequisites": ["m1_t2"],
          "learning_outcomes": [
            "Evaluate investment projects",
            "Apply NPV and IRR"
          ],
          "content": "## Capital Budgeting\nProcess of evaluating long-term investment decisions.\n\n### Techniques\n- Net Present Value (NPV)\n- Internal Rate of Return (IRR)\n- Payback Period\n\n### NPV Rule\nAccept if NPV > 0\n\n### Importance\nEnsures profitable investment decisions.",
          "examples": ["Factory expansion", "Buying new machinery"],
          "common_mistakes": [
            "Ignoring cash flows",
            "Focusing only on payback"
          ],
          "qna": [
            {
              "q": "What is capital budgeting?",
              "a": "Evaluating long-term investments."
            },
            {
              "q": "What is NPV?",
              "a": "Difference between inflow and outflow."
            },
            { "q": "IRR?", "a": "Rate where NPV is zero." },
            { "q": "Payback?", "a": "Time to recover investment." },
            { "q": "Decision rule?", "a": "Accept if NPV positive." }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
