            { "q": "What is cost of capital?", "a": "Required return." },
            { "q": "Types?", "a": "Equity and debt." },
            { "q": "Why important?", "a": "Investment decisions." },
            { "q": "Example?", "a": "Loan interest." },
            { "q": "Risk?", "a": "Wrong valuation." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic_id": "t2",
          "title": "Weighted Average Cost of Capital (WACC)",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "estimated_time": "25 min",
          "prerequisites": ["t1"],
          "learning_outcomes": [
            "Calculate WACC",
            "Apply in project evaluation"
          ],
          "content": "## WACC\nWeighted average of cost of equity and debt.\n\n### Formula\nWACC = (E/V × Re) + (D/V × Rd)\n\n### Importance\nUsed as hurdle rate.",
